<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="title">What about &lt;details&gt;?</h3>
<p>This element attempts to match the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLDetailsElement" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><code>HTMLDetailsElement</code></a> interface as close as possible so when browser support for <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> is sufficient it will be removed from M- in favor of the native element. Breaking changes should be limited to just the "m-" prefix.</p>
<h3 id="necessary">Ask yourself if the content is necessary</h3>
<p>Although Details and <a href="/accordion">Accordion</a> are great tools for progressive disclosure, you should always consider if the hidden content is necessary or if it could just be removed altogether.</p>
<h3>Clickable elements inside summary</h3>
<p>Sometimes <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> will need to include a button or other interactive element that should not toggle Details. Your event handler needs to use <code>stopPropogation</code>. Here's a rough example:</p>
<code-sample>
  <script>
    // Clicking "Clear" will not open/close Details
    const clearHistory = e => e.stopPropagation();
  </script>

  <template>
    <m-details>
      <summary>
        <span is="a">Show report history</span>
        <span  onclick="clearHistory(event)" is="a" class="mar-l-md">Clear</span>
      </summary>
      <p>Long list of report history...</p>
    </m-details>
  </template>
</code-sample>
